comm: starts with a good-length ball a foot outside off, decent carry through as Burns shoulders arms to it
closer to the off stump, 86mph and prodded down in front of square coming forwards
touch straighter and Burns clips nicely off his pads but can't get it past the dive of midwicket
off-stump line, slightly back of a length, hit on the pad trying to turn the ball to leg
pitched up and driven... through square leg, as you do. Thick inside edge on this, as Burns aimed down the ground, but it had plenty of pace on it and beat the attempts of fine leg to get round
full on off stump, 88mph and punched to mid-off, who intercepts cleanly on the bounce
full and swinging back, right into Warner's slot and he clubs it away meatily through midwicket, Adil Rashid gives chase all the way out to the rope and does well to save a run
fires this one down the leg side
pitched up, 86mph and ducking in on the stumps, Burns jams down on it
some shape on the ball for Wood but again it veers down the leg side
full, on off stump, punched back to the bowler
fired in on middle and leg stump, clipped to leg but again the midwicket fielder cuts it off
back of a length outside off stump, 88mph as Burns stands up tall and defends
length delivery on the stumps, Burns drives on the up back towards mid-on

the timing on this from Warner... he just leaned out to meet a length ball with the full bat face and almost picked up four out to deep extra cover, only for an equally brilliant dive from Morgan to pull it in inches from the rope
pitched up in the slot outside off, Burns throws the hands through a drive but mistimes it to cover
length in the channel, 87mph, this time Burns pierces the gap in the covers coming forwards
angled in towards the pads, closes the face and works to midwicket
good length, outside off stump, drives on the up but it bounces short of mid-off
back of a length, this time Burns respectfully blocks back down the track
lovely shot from Warner, too full and wide from Wood and lashed away through the covers, getting low and on to the front foot
better length, Wood is working up some pace, driven into the ground off the back foot but Taylor cuts it off leaping at point
fullish, little bit of width on offer again, this time pushed into a gap in the covers for a comfortable two
length delivery, starts on middle and leg and swerves towards slip, Warner lets it go
touch short, around the line of off, defended in front of square
full and straight from Wood, 86mph and driven back down the track, Wood takes a sharp catch on the bounce in his follow through
slightly overpitched, Burns watches it under his eyes and executes a princely straight drive... straight into the stumps at the other end, it deflects to mid-on and they don't even get a single
slower-ball bouncer from Finn, the batsman mistimes a pull to the leg side and it bounces down to theside of the wicket
on the stumps, attempted flick into the leg side, uppish but not to hand
on the stumps and pushed back down the track
short of a length, Warner sits watchfully in the crease and shows it a straight bat in defence
fuller, 81mph outside off stump, Warner drives but it comes off the toe and dribbles to mid-off
good length outside off, Burns leans into a square drive, finds cover point
touch short, 86mph outside off, punched down the ground to mid-off

pitched up and Burns continues to show aggression, steering the ball towards gully where Stokes takes an excellent diving catch... Was it a bump ball? The umpires aren't sure so they send it upstairs... Yes, doesn't take long to confirm, squeezed out off the bottom of the bat into the ground
slightly full and wide and thrashed away through the covers, that's a stroke of intent from Burns, getting forward and showing fast hands to hit the ball hard in front of square
pitched up and driven again, this time the ball squirts to backward point
touch short and straight and Burns hoicks it up and away over the leg side, in the air but safely out towards deep midwicket
around the line of off, length delivery, Burns taps it square
on the pads, flicked away past midwicket this time for a couple more to Burns
length in the channel, wide enough to glide comfortably down to third man for a single - there's a bit of strike rotation, Sudip
touch short on off stump, Warner blocks into the covers
back of a length, on the body, Warner nudges to leg and Moeen runs around from mid-on to keep them to one
not all that short, 85mph and pulled in the air, out towards deep square leg but it lands a few yards in front of Woakes
pitched up outside the line of off, leans out and drives to cover
angled in on thetumps, worked off the pads but finds midwicket again
short, 85mph and pulled, via a bottom edge, past short fine leg for a couple
length, middle and off stump, punched on the up towards mid-on
not a bad ball this, but it's supremely well placed through backward point, just made a little room and angled the bat, steered it wide of third man to pick up four
gets away with this, tries to hit a length ball down the ground, maybe beaten for pace a touch and a thick edge balloons over cover
touch back of a length, slightly straight and dabbed down to the leg side
very disciplined from Finn so far, excellent length and very little width on offer, Warner drops the ball into the covers for one
Burns looking increasingly fluent now, steps out and lofts a fractionally full delivery h-i-g-h over mid-off and away to the fence
draws his length back, tucked through backward square
another boundary, this time just a flick around the corner from Warner, slightly short and straight and whipped off the hips, beats deep square leg - 50 up for Australia
rolls his fingers over this, deceives Warner, who swings across the line and misses
full and straight, up in the blockhole, dug out towards mid-on
Burns moves to leg, Woakes follows him and fires the ball in at 86mph, clipped to midwicket
length ball, 87mph on middle and leg, Burns doesn't quite middle a golf shot past mid-on but Wood has a testing chase out to the rope, does really well to get there and prevent four
tight line, on the stumps, defended into the off side

very full, Warner thumps it straight back... and Woakes drops it, an instinctive reaction as the ball flew to the left of his head, got both hands there but couldn't hold on. Incredibly tough chance, and he's actually taken a nasty blow to the hand
angled across, length ball outside off, dabbed into the covers
gives it some air, outside off and Burns pushes to backward point, not taken cleanly diving forwards and they get one
floated up, on the pads, Warner tucks one through square
nicely bowled, bit of dip as Burns uses the feet, gets out and drives to long-off
tossed up, this is the googly, Warner stays back and tentatively pushes off his legs
pushed across outside off, possibly another wonrg'un, cut through backward point for a couple
flatter, faster and steered to gully off the back foot
slightly back of a lenfgth on the stumps, hits the thigh pad as Burns plays back
outside the line of off, back-foot drive to the man in the covers
bit of extra zip from Woakes, banging the ball in and it climbs past Burns' flailing bat, clocked at 87mph but that certainly beat him
good length, little bit of width for Burns to guide one to third man
tight lines, Warner sits in the crease and defends
well bowled, back of a length and Warner has to ride it, steered to backward point - just one off the over
tossed up, Burns launches into it and is lucky that his connection was so poor the ball bounced well short of mid-on
on the stumps, skips out again and hacks to leg, along the carpet and mid-on has to dive to his right this time, keeps them to one
tossed up and spinning down the leg side as Warner tries to sweep, not far from hitting leg stump, that
pushed across the lefty, tapped square
dragged down slightly as Warner attacks, tries to loft down the ground and skews the ball wide of mid-off, in the air but couldn't get to it, runs away for four
flatter on the stumps, possibly a googly, Warner shows it a watchful straight bat
hammers the ball in back of a length, worked through backward square for one
cutter, Warner picks it, the ball sits up outside off and he flat-bats it away through the covers, another boundary for Davey Dubya
tighter line, length on off stump, defended this time
pitched up outside the line of off, leans out and steers through point to the sweeper
Burns advances down the pitch early and Woakes spots it and bounces him, well directed and he has to pull out of his stroke, jerking his head away to the left as the ball flies through
short again, over the stumps and pulled down to fine leg
tossed up legbreak, some slow turn for Rashid but Burns gets out and lofts it cleanly over the infield, no one out and long-on and it bounces away to the rope
slower, outside off, tapped into the covers

Rashid strikes as Burns hits a full toss straight back to him! Oh dear, Burns has fizzled out, spoilt for choice and he ended up slicing the ball down the track at waist height, Rashid happily accepting the gift to break a very decent opening stand
length ball, straightening on the stumps, goes back and defneds
tossed up outside off, sits back and taps one into the covers to get going
flatter, pushed through with some over spin, Warner nudges it off his pads into a gap on the leg side
back of a length, outside off stump, Warner angles the bat and steers towards point
fuller, comes forward and punches a drive through the covers
short and at the body, 86mph, worked off the hips through square for a single
good length, just outside off, drops back and guides the ball to backward point
Warner groans in frustration as he pushes a length ball straight to extra cover
touch shorter, again he angles the bat and this time manages to swat one through the covers to the sweeper
Rashid tosses the ball up, Warner skips out and gets to the pitch, flays the ball away through the covers, powerful blow for four
flighted, on the stumps,m worked into a gap on the leg side
gives it some air, Smith flicks to leg but can't get it through the infield
full, slightly wide and driven coming forwards, Morgan throws himself horizontally to cut it off at short extra cover
flicked off the legs, very wristy stroke from Smith, manages to get it past backward square leg and doesn't give deep midwicket a chance to get round and cut it off
tossed up outside off, punched down the ground
full and straight, flicked down to long-on with a whip of the bottom hand
that comes out as a big full toss, but Warner misses out as he charges down the pitch and gets a thick edge into his pads
good work by Moeen in his follow through as he quick gets across to cut off a sweetly-struck drive
slightly shorter, he goes back and drives wide of cover
a little extra bounce than Smith expected, and it spun, as he flicks to the leg side
can't beat square leg as he turns this away with a closed face...steady start for Moeenb
drops a touch short with his first delivery and that's a superb piece of timing and placement as he cuts it off the front foot wide of cover
tighter to off stump, back of a length, pushed square to the off side
comes round the wicket, angled in from short of a length, pushed into space on the off side
short of a length outside off, Smith opens the face and runs down to third man
worked away from off stump to midwicket
fuller to end the over, targeting the stumps at 88mph, driven firmly to mid-off
very full, at the block hole, dug out back to the bowler
again he finds Moeen as he flicks a full delivery back down the pitch
just outside off, pushed into the covers
a fraction shorter, Smith forces off the back foot to midwicket
nearly gets a leading edge back to the bowler, looking to work a delivery from around off stump through the leg side but didn't carry to Moeen to his left
driven down the ground to long-on, the only run off the over and it brings up Australia's hundred
short of a length outside off, worked around the corner behind square
uses his feet, Stokes may have seen him coming and dragged the length back, Warner drives towards mid-off
short again, angled into the body, Smith pulls down to long leg
nearly dragged on, a slightly slower ball at 79mph, a full length and Warner pushed forward and it getting a thick inside edge wide of leg stump
a compact drive on the up, wide of cover and wide of the sweeper behind him
gets inside the line of a short delivery, aims to work through the leg side but doesn't make a clean contact
round the wicket, full at the stumps, Warner again skipping down the pitch and drives to long-off
swift footwork now from Smith as he gets to the pitch and flicks to deep midwicket
comes forward and pushes back to the bowler
flicked from off stump down to long-on
whipped off the back foot to deep midwicket
dragged down short, Warner swivels on a pull but picks out Taylor at deep square who is quick across the ground
full from round the wicket, squeezed just to the left of mid-on and Warner gets the single he needs for a 57-ball fifty
full outside off, 79mph, driven to cover
full and wider outside off, Smith drives over the top of it...didn't quite get out towards the ball, playing well away from his body
full again, almost a yorker, jabbed back to the bowler
shorter in length outside off, Smith fetches it into the leg side and finds square leg
full and wide, driven off an open face down to third man
plenty of bottom hand as he whips a full ball out to deep midwicket
round the wicket, Warner down the pitch and drives back to the bowler
good placement as he flicks this along the ground through midwicket and wide of long-on
driven down to long-off
a wider line outside off, pushed to the covers
another one sent along the ground to deep midwicket
comes forward to a slower ball at 74mph, drives to cover
gets this through the off side, not perfectly timed as he drives on the up but it splits cover and mid-off then races across a fast outfield
this drive was more sweetly struck, but he picked out Moeen in the ring although he parried it for a single
short outside off, 77mph, pulled in front of square with a roll of the wrists...Stokes holding back his pace quite regularly
angled in from outside off, plays with a closed face wide of mid-on
short again around off stump, 87mph this time, Warner swats it out to deep square leg
comes down on the line of leg stump to open up the off side then drives to long-off
flicked from off stump to deep midwicket
goes back to a shorter delivery and drives wide of deep cover who can't stop the second
tight run this time! Warner pushed into the leg side this time, Morgan made an excellent save at midwicket and, for a moment, there was hesitation from Warner but he was okay in the end
this time Roy at midwicket dives to his left but can't quite stop this cleanly...he's pretty close
opens his stance then drives straight to short cover
starts outside leg stump and gets flicked away to deep square leg

he's got the breakthrough again! Credit to Morgan, as well as Rashid. Brave enough to toss the ball up, might have been a googly, Warner went for a drive and it skews off a thick outside edge to short third man
on the stumps, pushed to the off side
whips a full ball to mid-on...a direct hit from mid-on at the non-striker's end, Smith had to get around Rashid to get his foot across the line
comes down the pitch and works to the leg side
dragged down short, Bailey rocks back and pulls through midwicket
uses his feet and flicks to midwicket
defended back to the bowler
turned to deep backward square
that's a big full toss outside off but it only costs a single as Bailey clubs to long-on
pitches this one nicely at off stump, driven firmly to the covers where Taylor is fairly deep
goes back in the crease and tucks a shorter ball through square...swift running this time
driven firmly to mid-on
waits for the turn outside off and dabs towards point
short outside off, cut to deep cover
sweeps a delivery on leg stump firmly to deep square
well bowled, good googly from Rashid and Bailey didn't read it...coming forward and gets an inside edge into his front pad
that's a good response! Dispatches a friendly full toss over long-on for the first six of the day. Rashid doesn't get away with this one
full at off stump, 84mph, defended firmly to cover
short of a length outside off, worked to square leg

edged through the vacant slip cordon and Finn can't cut it off at third man...an odd shot from Smith, trying to work a pretty wide ball through the leg side. Well, I say odd. Probably quite normal for him
driven square through the off side, more good running
just short! Nearly finds mid-on. Smith driving at a full ball, the bat face closes, but it lands a few inches in front of Rashid
now he finds Rashid with a punchy drive all along the ground
uses his feet, takes a thickish inside edge through short fine leg
full at middle and leg, defended to the on side
another full toss which is swung down to long on
misses his cut and gets beaten under the bottom edge as this slides on
and now it's Smith's turn for a six over long-on, used his feet and lofted with a bit of bottom hand well clear of the rope

another full toss, another wicket! Would you believe it! Smith is furious with himself. Was a juicy full toss, Smith was aiming to clear the deep midwicket boundary but couldn't get it wide, or over, Ben Stokes. That's a waste from the Australian captain
what a fantastic piece of timing first ball, a back-of-a-length delivery outside off and Maxwell elegantly drives it off the back foot through the covers and wide of the sweeper. Superb.
fuller ball, at off stump, 87mph and drives firmly to mid-off
angled into leg stump, Maxwell gets inside the line and tucks to long leg
pulls a short-of-a-length delivery from outside off to long leg
short again, Bailey quick onto the pull and it's again wide enough of long leg for a brace
terrific stroke, full outside off, Bailey drives on the up wide of mid-off...clean through the line. Good counterpunch in that over
full outside off, driven to the covers where Morgan springs to his right but the ball escapes for a single

and another! Excellent stuff from Rashid. A quicker ball, skids on and just grips a little, Bailey on the back foot aiming through the leg side, misses his shot and is struck on the back leg in front of middle. Nothing flukey about that one.
full outside off, driven to long-off
driven into the covers
beaten outside off as this spins, Maxwell aiming a booming drive through the covers
quick ball outside off, touch short, Maxwell cuts strongly and it goes behind point but the sweeper - Hales - is just able to cut it off
full and straight, 85mph, flicked to deep midwicket
on middle and off, 88mph, defended to the covers
runs this off the outside edge down to third man
full at off stump, good pace, played firmly back to Wood in his follow through
short outside off, driven from the back foot through the covers
accurate delivery to finish the over, full at off stump, Watson defends on the front foot
full at off stump, driven down the ground
pulled down short, flipped off the back foot to long-on
cut away from outside off through point
outside leg stump, flicked to backward square leg
tossed up a little more, a controlled loft over cover...nice control from Maxwell
drilled back past the bowler who flings out a hand
length ball outside off, 86mph and it rushes on to the bat as Watson pushes square
good length, drops back outside off and pushes one through point

down the leg side, Maxwell flicks at it... does Buttler take the catch? Was there an edge? Joel Wilson raises his finger and, after some discussion between Maxwell, Watson and the umpires, the batsman heads off. The Big Show leaves the stage early, as replays confirm both the catch and a thin edge. Wood has a wicket, in slightly fortuitous circumstances
pitched up and driven hard, to the diving short extra cover, caught on a bump ball
length on the stumps and blocked into the leg side
feisty bumper from Wood, 86mph but it was zeroing in on the top of Wade's block, he thought about pulling before pirouetting out of the way
tossed up, outside off and Watson pushes forward warily in defence
flatter, this is the googly, plays back and gets the inside half of the bat on it
tossed up outside the line, comes forward and pushes one down the ground
topspinner, on middle and off, Wade goes back in the crease to defend
goes down on one knee, pre-empting a paddle sweep, fails to connect and it hits the pad, outside the line

pushed into the covers, Stokes swoops... and Watson is run out by a mile! What was Wade thinking?! Never a run there and Stokes only had to return the ball over the stumps, Buttler completed the job and Watson was barely ambling into shot
round the wicket, tossed up around the line of off, Wade plunges forward to defend
angled in with the arm, noises of interest from the bowler as Wade again prods forward
tossed up, shuffles down the pitch, pushes a single through extra cover
over the wicket, Marsh taps it back down the track
pushed through, again pushed back to the bowler
tossed up on off stump, this time Marsh works the ball back past Moeen to long-on
short on the stumps, drops back and nudges through square leg
tight line on off stump, leans out to block a length delivery
that's nicely played, not overly full but Wade steps out and strokes it down the ground, fine of mid-off - that's the Aussie 200, as well
waits in the crease and chops the ball to point
bit of width, Wades stays low and flashes the ball through point, there's a man in the deep to receive
length, around off stump, closes the face and turns to leg
flighted, drifting towards middle and leg, blocked to the on side
another boundary for Wade, reaches out and paddles a low full toss around the corner, gets it down to fine leg for four
angled in with the arm, pushed into a gap
goes over the wicket, pushed through outside off, turned short on the leg side
tossed up, gets on to the front foot and drives wide of long-off for a couple
that's a good shot, skips out and lofts over extra cover, knows there's not a man out there and the ball skips away to the rope
pushed across the lefty, who steers one through the covers
shortish, tries to pull and the ball deflects off bottom and edge and thigh pad
pushed back down the track

back of a length, Wade surfs the wave and gets away with a cut beyond the diving Stokes at backward point... He got his fingertips to the ball but there was just enough pace and height to clear the fielder and find the boundary
slightly too full and straight and skelped through midwicket this time, another punchy stroke from Wade, who's motoring at a run a ball
length ball, tight to the off stump, opens the face and steers to backward point, followed by a loud "No run!"
length ball outside off, Marsh can only bunt it back to the bowler
shortish, 86mph and over the stumps, worked away through backward square leg for one
back of a length outside off, tapped in front of square from the crease
straighter line and Wade flicks busily to leg, finds a gap, scurries off for a single
shortish ball, hits Marsh on the gloves as he turns to leg, Buttler chases after it and prevents a run
short and wide and lashed through the covers to spoil an otherwise spotless over... Marsh didn't need telling what to do with that
round the wicket, pitched up outside off but Wade's drive finds the man at point
dug in short, Wade splices a pull over the man at midwicket, bounces on the edge of the circle and they get a couple
Wade is giving this innings the 'oompetus' it needed, seizes on a short ball and slashes it away through backward point, not far from being caught but fortune favours this brave once again
full and straight, Wade squeezes down on it, Stokes appeals for lbw... Not sure if it was bat on pad first but the umpire isn't interested. Might have been heading down the leg side anyway
banged in short and pulled smartly, away through backward square to the sweeper
length on off stump, Marsh hops across and shovels one more through midwicket
full outside off, drilled along the ground to mid-off
length on off stump, Marsh pushes uppishly, bounces towards mid-off... and Morgan scores a direct hit at the non-striker's end. But Marsh was in
round the wicket, dug in short but Wade walks across and rattles the ball through backward square, using his angles well - another boundary
full toss on middle and leg, helps it on its way down to fine leg
slower ball, on leg stump, Marsh waits and clips through backward square - 50 stand up, at more than a run a ball
good length, whipped off the stumps through midwicket
slower ball, fetched from wide of the stumps down the ground, muscular blow from Marsh but it bounces short of long-on
round the wicket, low full toss at 87mph, wide of the stumps but sliced along the ground to backward point
full toss this time, just about dips below waist height as Wade shovels it to leg
strays slightly leg side but Marsh misses with a glance, rolls away off the pad
slower ball, wide of the stumps, Wade drags down on it, picks up a couple wide of long-on
another slower delivery but Stokes gets this wrong, well down the leg side and although Wade top edges a swipe it flies away fine of the fielder on the ring and runs for four to finish the over
full on the stumps, dug out towards long-on for a single
skips out early and Woakes goes full and wide, 88mph and it only needs a scrape of bat to fly away through third man, goes quickly to the fence
fullish, on the pads, Wade uses the pace again and whips one through backward square
tries to advance, a length ball beats him for pace slightly, slugged into the ground towards long-on
attempted yorker from Woakes, not quite full enough but Wade only manages to dig out a single into the leg side
full and straight, again Marsh heaves across the line, gets a thick inside edge but they run well to deep midwicket and pick up two
length ball, taking some pace off, wide enough for Wade to cut through the covers for one
pitched right up towards the blockhole, Marsh mistimes a swing and gets an inside edge on to his pad, deflects wide of the keeper
pitched up, Wades scampers out of his crease, pushes one through the off side
fires the ball in on leg stump, another decent attempted yorker, squeezed back down the ground to long-on
on the stumps, a slower ball, Wade heaves at it, gets a thick inside edge through square and hustles back for two to bring up a 40-ball half-century that has been a tonic for Australia's innings
full outside off, Wade backs away and larrups the ball down the ground... through Woakes at mid-off, the misfield again gives them a boundary off the final ball
slower delivery from Woakes, flicked away through backward square
yorker, fired in at 87mph, driven firmly to mid-off and that prevents them from running
full and wide this time, Wade has to reach for it, gets a bottom edge towards point
Woakes continues to pepper the blockhole, Marsh can't get under it, sends the ball bobbling to long-on
cute from Wade, and effective too, moving well outside off  and ramping the ball over short fine leg, finds the boundary
Wade backs away and Woakes skims one through full on the edge of the tramlines - a dot at the death
full and straight, shovelled down the ground
Wades steps away and rifles the ball over mid-off! Wood not quite full enough and he's crashed down the ground
pulled, in the air... and Hales can't take it diving forwards, bounces over the rope for four to deep backward square leg
on the pads, whipped away through deep midwicket
fullish, Marsh plugs the ball down the ground to long-off
pitched up, Wade clubs the ball savagely down the ground, long-on keeps them to two
full and straight, dug out past the bowler, towards long-on and they again race back for two
steps to leg, Woakes targets the feet, sends the ball through Marsh's legs as he swings across the line... Nutmeg!
pitched up on the stumps at 88mph, drilled down the ground to long-off
steps to off, he's ready for the yorker and digs it out firmly back past Woakes, who can't get down in his follow through - just a single as long-off runs across
Marsh advances, cuts down the angle, takes the ball on the full... and whistles it straight back over the fence for six! A mighty swipe down the ground takes Australia above 300
fires this in, Marsh heaves to the leg side, that will be just a single to finish the innings
good start, on a length at middle and off, Roy defends and gets a thick inside edge into his pads
a little shorter this time, 90mph, Roy defends on the back foot
nice from Starc as he draws Roy onto the front foot with a fuller delivery, Roy a little hesitant
short on leg stump, pulled one bounce to long leg
on middle and leg, worked into the on side
neat start for Hales as he comes forward into a fullish delivery angled across, drives on the up and threads the gap through cover. Excellent timing.
back of a length at off stump, 87mph, defended square into the covers
defended towards mid-on
nice timing from Roy this time, flicks a back-of-a-length delivery from around middle and off wide of square leg
goes fuller at off stump, Roy comes forward and drives sweetly to mid-on
shorter again and Roy uses his bottom hand to flick it towards mid-on
more of a heave through square leg this time, Roy not afraid to get onto the front foot against decent pace
another boundary for Hales as he drives strongly square of the wicket as Starc pushes the ball across him
out with a hit! Maxwell at cover. Hales pushed off the back foot and picked out the wrong man to take on. Maxwell moved to his right, picked up one hand but missed with a single stump to aim at
just a flip off the hip! Lovely stroke from Roy, a short-of-a-length delivery on his hip which he picks up with a effortless flick behind square...lands just in front of the rope
takes the pad down the leg side, Wade gets across
dropped? Or was it short? Roy comes forward and bunts the delivery towards mid-on and, yes, it landed just short of Bailey as he dived forward
oh, that's lovely from Roy, he takes a stride forward and effortlessly drives on the up wide of mid-off...using the pace
fullish on middle, defended square into the covers
that's a sharp bouncer at 87mph, good line over middle but Hale does well to get out of the line
short of a length at off stump, driven off the back foot to mid-off
angling back into Hales a touch, trying to cramp him for room, Hales plays to mid-off again
this one is a touch fuller, Hales comes onto the front foot and pings it with a drive straight to the fielder
another bouncer, over off stump, Hales ducks and that's a maiden...the first of the day
comes forward and drives to cover
full at the stumps, 90mph, played to mid-off
pulls the length back and pushes it across Roy who opens the face and guides to third man
it's a top edge, but goes all the way! Dropped in short by Starc, Hales pulled from quite a low position, got well underneath it but a healthy enough edge that it clears deep square
that's much better! A stinging straight drive as Starc then goes for the fuller, met with a full face and a punchy shot
another powerful drive as Hales strides forward but Cummins at mid-off is just able to cut this off
beats him with a short-of-a-length delivery which he tries to run to third man...doesn't carry to Wade
on off stump, 88mph, defend
now Roy goes for the hook and he, too, gets a big top edge...this one goes much finer than Hales' and doesn't quite clear the rope
adjusts to a fuller length, defended with bat and pad together
another short ball and this time it's pulled more convincingly, but he only gets a single as he finds deep square leg
width outside off but it doesn't cost him as Hales drives to point
back of a length outside off, played to the covers
on the back foot, punched firmly to cover
full outside off, 91mph, driven in the air backward point and wide of third man
full outside off, left alone (yep, a leave)
sweetly driven on the up to cover
finds the gap again, Roy comes forward to a 92mph delivery and powers it on the up wide of mid-off
back of a length at off stump, driven square to point
another crunching drive, this time down the on-side of the stumps as Coulter-Nile gets a touch straighter, but mid-on cuts it off with a dive
full at off stump, Roy is forward and defends
dragged down short, you could hear a cry of 'no' from the bowler even before Roy had pulled it behind square for another boundary...fine leg had come inside the circle, too
on a length outside off, cut down to third man
a yorker at off stump, dug out square
feels for this a little outside off, it's 91mph, but is pushed safely enough into the covers
on off stump, defended
walks into a defensive shot and plays to cover
a strong drive off the back foot but he picks out cover
a touch fuller this time, tight line at off stump, consistently above 90mph
angled into the pads, misses his attempt to flick it away so that's another maiden
angled into the pads, flicked to deep square
very neatly played, pushed towards leg stump, Roy gets inside the line and tucks it fine of short fine-leg inside the circle
on the pads again, and it's equally costly as Roy flicks it a little squarer this time, the other side of short fine-leg, and deep square can't get around
a shorter delivery which Roy goes to pull and misses, gets a blow on the top of the leg
gets onto off stump for the first time, played square to backward point
full at off stump, driven to short cover
gets beaten outside off as he tries to play this through the off side
full outside off, driven through the off side and there's a sweeper out now
onto the front foot and drives a full ball, at 92mph, to the covers
delicate touch this time as he just carefully opens the face and runs a back-of-a-length delivery fine of third man
now he's short on leg stump, Roy uses the pace - 93mph of it - and pulls it off his hip to fine leg
adjusts the line back outside off, very full, driven to the covers
back of a length, driven off the back foot to cover
breakthrough! Hales picks out midwicket. A short ball from Marsh, Hales latches on but pinged it straight to Watson. A bit of a giveaway from Hales.
full and straight, pushed to mid-on
comes forward and defends to cover
a touch shorter, Taylor shuffles across the crease and defends
comes down the pitch, Marsh fires in a delivery at his feet which Taylor somewhat awkwardly digs out
angled into the pads, flicked to long leg
opens the face outside off and Warner allows it through his hands at backward point to allow Taylor off the mark
full at off stump, defended
waits for his outside off, plays it late with a cut shot, sends it wide of third man and that's his maiden ODI fifty
well forward and pushes to backward point
gets across outside off and works a full delivery towards mid-on who is too deep to prevent the single
glided down to third man
gets across his stumps and shovels a shorter delivery to the leg side
angled down the leg side...first wide of the innings, just the third of the day

back on the stumps but he's met with a wonderful piece of timing as Roy flicks strongly with his bottom hand and sends it rocketing through midwicket. That was pure timing. Played at the top of the bounce.
on the pads again, poor line, tucked to deep square
blimey, Taylor bursts out of his shell by skipping down the pitch and lofting Marsh straight back over his head...a lovely clean strike, strong bottom hand
stays in his crease this time and angles a length delivery to third man
full at off stump, driven back to the bowler
worked down to third man again
full at off stump, gets an edge but it falls short of Wade, walking into the shot
worked off the pads to deep midwicket
comes forward and drives to deep cover
full at off stump, Taylor defends into the covers
comes down the pitch and then flat-bat pulls to deep square
keeps getting onto leg stump, flicked off the pads to deep square
dropped in short and pulled over midwicket, not quite out of the middle
back-cut to third man
quickly onto a short ball, that's a powerful pull which Burns can't cut off at deep square despite making good ground to it
short again and another whippy pull, this time of the front foot through midwicket
more whippage from Roy, gets across the crease and takes this from around middle and off to long leg
fuller, angled into the pads, tucked to midwicket
on off stump, pushed towards mid-on
coming at the bowler again, flicks off the pads through square leg
on middle and off, played to the covers
that's a bit of a heave, takes a full delivery from off stump and picks out midwicket
round the wicket, dobbed on the pads and nurdled through the leg side
tossed up, on the stumps, leans out and tucks the ball through square, Roy comes haring back for a second
floated on middle and leg, worked back down the ground to long-on
floated across towards the off stump, Taylor creeps out and drills one more to long-off

steps away and drives, in the air... and taken at point! Maxwell has got Roy, slicing a shot straight to the fielder. Might have skidded on a bit as he was trying to force the ball over the off side - maybe an unnecessary risk, with singles coming regularly, but that's the game and Roy's a goner
angled in with the arm and defended from the crease
dug in short and Taylor is whiplash-fast through a pull shot, looks to have bisected deep square and fine leg but an excellent sliding stop prevents four
on the stumps, Taylor hops into line and defends
length outside off, 91mph from Cummins, Taylor pushes into the covers
pitched up, driven back along the ground, Cummins stretches to stop it in his follow through
full on off stump, this is clocked at above 92mph, punched back to the bowler
pitched up around the line of off again, Taylor pushes along the ground to mid-off - excellent over from Cummins
round the wicket, angled in and tapped back on the off side
pushed through outside off, Morgan jumps back and cuts hard, finds backward point
tossed up around off, Morgan leans out and defends

kamikaze from Morgan! Takes on the man in the covers, rather like Wade in the Australia innings, and even the rapid Taylor is struggling, he throws himself for the line as the throw comes in low... but Wade can't take it cleanly and dislodges the bails with his gloves. Would have been extremely tight otherwise
pushed back down the ground past the bowler
length outside off, Morgan goes back and chops one in front of square into the deep
drops back outside off and steers a single in front of square
pitched up in the channel, Taylor throws the bat and gets a thin edge that bounces on its way through to the keeper
full again, Taylor whirs into action and punctures the ring on the off-side, gets it between two men and there's plenty on the stroke to take it away to the boundary
length, drifting towards leg stump, 92mph and Taylor is hit on the pads - Cummins belts out an appeal but was maybe a touch high too
fullish, outside off, Taylor's bat comes down at an angle and a thick edge rolls square
shuffles across and defends a length ball
darted in towards the pads, closes the face and tickles one wide of mid-on
goes over the wicket, tossed up and Taylor advances, hits the ball back to the bowler
skips out, not quite to the pitch but he hits up and through the line, gets it over mid-off and the ball bounces away for four
pushed back towards the bowler
pushed through on off stump, clipped back along the ground, Maxwell gets a hand to it but can't prevent a run
length outside off, Morgan cuts off the back foot but can't get it past point
over the top of off stump, nudged wide of mid-on for one
stays over the wicket, back of a length, waits on it and closes the face for one to midwicket
shuffles to off stump and turns one more into the leg side
Morgan gets an inside edge and it shaves the paint on off stump! Cummins has his hands on his head, Morgan gets four... The ball got up close and personal with the timber but there was not touching
drops back and chops the ball behind square
length ball, Morgan pushes it back towards mid-off
tossed up, Taylor uses the feet and pushes one to long-on
skidding on with the arm, Morgan stays back and plays late, chopping through the covers
on the stumps, can't get this one away
round the wicket to Taylor, tucked off his pads through square leg
angled in with the arm, Morgan works across the line for one more through midwicket
tight lines from Maxwell but these two are happy enough just totting up singles, another one clipped out to deep midwicket
pitched full on middle and off, there's an "oooh" from the bowler as Taylor walks in front of his stumps and whips to leg
length on off, 80mph and Morgan gets an inside edge between his legs, falls safely again and they pinch one
wicket to wicket from Watson, worked through backward square and this time they get back for two
good length on off stump, 84mph, blocked towards midwicket
sliding on to the pads, just a tickle of bat sends it skipping down to fine leg for a couple more
angled in, tapped short on the leg side
length ball, maybe rolling his fingers over it, Morgan prods back to the bowler, who tumbles over in his follow through
fullish, on middle stump, poked back down the track
beaten, bit of an anxious flail from Morgan, trying to cut when there wasn't the room
comes forward and gets the through the covers for a single
length, 86mph and tight outside off stump, played late and dabbed past short third man
on the stumps and defended - decent over from Coulter-Nile, though an asking rate of 6.5 won't perturb England yet
bit of luck for Taylor this time, giving Watson the charge and thick-edging past his stumps down to long leg

angling in, swipes across the line - and bowled 'im! Taylor advanced at the bowler again, played around a straight one and it clattered into the top of middle and leg. He falls for an industrious 49 and the pressure goes up another notch
pitched up outside off and blocked on the front foot
full, in the slot, Stokes leans out and drives gently towards mid-off
pushed across, he goes back and across and guides a single to third man
length ball outside off stump, 79mph, Morgan opens the face and runs one more through gully
pitched up, Morgan comes forward on off stump and punches through the covers
full outside off, tapped back along the ground
slightly short of a length, runs one down to third man
fullish, outside off, Morgan mistimes a drive coming forwards
pitched up and Morgan waltzes down the pitch, clubs the ball over mid-on and away! He's been content to bide his time but that was a positive move, nicely executed
Coulter-Nile goes back to a shortish length on off, Morgan toe-ends it in front of square
over the wicket, good length in the corridor, Stokes leans out and watches it through

full and straight, Stokes crunches it back in Starc's direction, he sticks out a left paw but can't cling on - tough to even call it a chance, umpire Michael Gough was already taking evasive action, it was hit that hard
pitched up and driven towards mid-off
full on the stumps, Stokes gets forward and clips the ball past the bowler along the ground this time
fullish, tailing in, Morgan taps it square
gets across and pushes a single into the covers
length delivery, on off stump, Stokes rocks back and swings wildly for a single to deep extra cover
tossed up, comes forward and pushes into a gap

down the leg side, Stokes tries to reverse sweep... Wade immediately throws the ball into the air and then signals for a review when it is not given on field; third umpire Kumar Dharmasena takes a look at several replays, including Hot Spot, and concludes that there was clear daylight between bat and ball. Well, Wade was convinced but no one else was... No Snicko on this occasion
skidding on with the arm, Stokes brings his bat down late
stays in the crease and pushes one through the covers
tossed up on the stumps, Morgan can't get this one away
played back down the pitch...a better spell, so far, from Starc
full at off stump, drilled back to the bowler
back of a length, Stokes can't find a gap as he drives to cover
angled in from short of a length, flicks out to deep square leg
beats him outside off as he plays over the top of the delivery
goes back into his crease and drives to cover
nearly through him! A quicker ball slides on, Stokes exposes his stumps but just manages to slice down onto it in time and gets runs to third man
dragged down a little short and Stokes is able to take out some frustration with a pull that beats deep midwicket...more effort than timing
cut out to deep cover
full at the stumps, eased back down the pitch
played out to extra cover
he finds midwicket! Not Stokes' most convincing innings. A full delivery, angled into the pads, and he flicks it straight to Joe Burns...silence around the ground
full at off stump, played to mid-on
super yorker! Just outside off stump, Buttler plays over the top of it...this is very testing now for England
over the wicket, tucked off the pads to the right of mid-on
full and and straight, worked behind square on the leg side
full outside off, driven out to deep cover
he manages to break free with a lofted drive over mid-off, full and quite floaty outside off and it allowed Morgan to free his arms
straightens his line, drags his length back, tucked into midwicket
cut away outside off, sends it wide of the cover sweeper...nice placement
beats him outside off, a full delivery, hint of movement away, Buttler's feet didn't move
pushed square to point
lovely delivery, bit of zip off the bit from Watson as it tails past the outside edge...Buttler playing with a slightly open face
worked off the hip down to long leg
just over backward point! Not far from the fielder, but it raced away to beat third man...Maxwell the man at backward point
gets onto off stump, 86mph, defended to mid-off
that's a confident shot from Morgan, a big stride forward into a fuller ball and drives wide of the cover sweeper
short of a length outside off, Morgan onto his toes and pushes to the off-side sweeper
tucks a straight delivery to midwicket...handy over for England
full outside off, driven to cover
flicks a straight delivery off his body to fine leg
gets well across his crease and fetches this from outside towards mid-on
uses his feet, Watson pulls the length back so Morgan just defends
huge moment! He's gloved it down the leg side going for the pull. The ball was there for the shot, short and outside leg stump, but it just glanced the glove through to Wade
on off stump, pushed to the covers

but he's gone now! England falling away. Full outside off, Buttler goes for the drive and just picks out mid-off inside the circle. That was loose from Buttler, needed to at least take a moment to assess after Morgan's departure

he's on a hat-trick! Short, angled down the leg side, Woakes goes for a paddle-turned-pull and gets a very thin glove through to Wade. One glove down the leg side can be unlucky, but two in four balls?
it's a big full toss! Aiming for a yorker. And Rashid almost leading-edges it to cover. Took him by surprise, the bat face closed
dragged wide outside off
tight on off stump, 83mph, defended to the covers
a little fuller, played to the off side
that's a lovely way to get off the mark, an on-the-up drive through the off side, the sweeper had been brought up...nothing wrong with that at all
in the air, but short of mid-off! Full at the stumps, Moeen pushes firmly, perhaps the ball stopped a little, and it ballooned back past the bowler
opens the face and places this through the off side...200 up for England, but a lot of damage done of late
tries to angle a straight delivery into an off-side gap but finds point
edged, wide of Wade! It wasn't catch, the ball died off the edge, landed in front of Wade's out-stretched right glove
driven to backward point
more control in his from Rashid, dabbed away from outside off wide of Wade and fine of third man but he's able to scoot around the rope
resumes with a full toss which Moeen bunts to midwicket
a lower full toss this time, and a lovely piece of timing down the ground with a straight drive
speared down the leg side, sends Wade diving to his right and provides a bonus run and bonus delivery
keeping it full, Moeen on-drives again, in the air for a distance but short of mid-on
driven to the covers
touch shorter outside off, drives with an open face to point
short, still, and Moeen tries to force it off the back foot but it comes high off the bat and loops slowly towards mid-off
opens the face, finds backward point but he just had to move far enough to his left to allow the single
back of a length outside off, steered to point
another flowing drive from Moeen, this was a back-of-a-length delivery but he struck through the line and send it straight down the ground
fuller from Cummins, Moeen drives again and this time it squirts off the inner part of the part towards mid-on
big appeal for lbw, Rashid hammered on the boot by a low full toss, appeared to be sliding down the leg side
just over cover, Moeen driving on the up again outside off
regulation stuff, full outside off, nicked to the keeper...Starc came round the wicket and there's just a hint of it moving away from Rashid as he drives. Neat, low catch
stays round the wicket, full at the stumps, defended
driven in the air but doesn't quite reach short cover
well, you say nice things...a low full toss outside off, Wood gets the bottom of the bat into the ground wide of slip
full and straight, more movement late at the batsman, Wood somehow works it through cover
well, he's certainly driving well at the moment. Wasn't a bad ball at all, on a length outside off, he just elegantly pierced the gap between cover and mid-off
full, 90mph, Wood pushes it down the ground
a bouncer at middle and off, Moeen pulls without quite being in control

short of a length, angled into the body, Wood takes a blow, the ball drops down by his feet and he gets called through by Moeen...Cummins follows through, collects then throws at Wood's end. Probably just safe
another well-directed bouncer, 88mph, and Moeen is actually through his shot and gets taken on the shoulder
terrific work by Cummins in his follow through, Moeen drilled the ball firmly but Cummins stuck out his right hand

and that's just about that! The short ball does the trick. Got fed up feeding Moeen's drive, went short and it's worked. Moeen goes for the pull, comes off the toe end, goes high but not very far and midwicket settles underneath it
round the wicket, full and straight, squirts away square
short, angled into the body, pulled to deep square
full and straight, 91mph, jabbed out
he ducks into a short ball, takes it in the ribcage
short again, Finn gets another blow - on the gloves this time

not staying in line this time, backs away to leg and swings at the full delivery, edges towards third man where Burns makes a terrific effort to cut it off. Has he done? Body, ball and boundary are all close together. He may be okay. Yep, super work
full and straight, dug out in the air over cover
giving himself more room, slogged into the leg side and just finds midwicket
moves to the leg side again, Cummins follows him with a short one which is flapped over midwicket
that's sprayed short and way down the leg side
back of a length, nudged to the leg side...Finn back on strike
a low full toss is hammered towards mid-on
a slower ball, 73mph, Finn swings hard and is almost through his shot
standing on, or outside leg stump, he clubs a full delivery to mid-on
better connection this time, but it's straight at mid-on
good yorker, but it is squeezed off the outside edge wide of slip
a big swing and a miss
clubs a low full toss towards mid-on...lot of effort in Finn's shots without much reward
full from round the wicket, angled into Wood who drives to mid-on
full, following the batsman outside leg, swung reasonably cleanly over midwicket
completely defeated by a slower ball, Finn had almost spun around to see the ball reach Wade
that's all over! Finn misses a wild swing to leg and Cummins was straight. Job done.
